      <exercise id="fs-id1169738162964" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1169736994002">   
          <para id="import-auto-id1169737965301">Verify that the units of <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>Δ</m:mn><m:mi fontstyle="italic">Φ</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ΔΦ} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>/ <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>Δ</m:mn><m:mi fontstyle="italic">t</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{Δt} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> are volts. That is, show that <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>T</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">⋅</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>m</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mn>2</m:mn></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:mtext>s</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mn>1 V</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{1`T cdot m rSup { size 8{2} } /s=1`V} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</para></problem></exercise><exercise id="fs-id1169738145077" type="problems-exercises">
