      <exercise id="fs-id1169738060612"><problem id="fs-id1169738060613">    <para id="import-auto-id1169738036172">A voltage is induced by rotating a 1000-turn, 20.0 cm diameter coil in the Earth’s <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mn>5</m:mn><m:mtext>.</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>00</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">×</m:mo><m:msup><m:mtext>10</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>5</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:msup></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>T</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{5 "." "00" times "10" rSup { size 8{ - 5} } `T} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> magnetic field. What average voltage is induced, given the plane of the coil is originally perpendicular to the Earth’s field and is rotated to be parallel to the field in 10.0 ms?</para></problem>
